<p>There are 2 elements on the same view. One is removed from DOM at the same time when other is inserted.</p>  <p>I want to use anchor animation to morph between those 2 elements.</p>  <p><strong>HTML</strong></p>  <pre><code>&lt;button ng-click="showDiv = !showDiv"&gt;Anchor Animation&lt;/button&gt;  &lt;div ng-if="!showDiv" ng-animate-ref="anchor1" class="anchor1-animation" style="position:absolute; left:150px; top:90px; background:#FE367F; width:50px; height:50px"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div ng-if="showDiv" ng-animate-ref="anchor1" class="anchor1-animation" style="position:absolute; right:50px; top:250px; background:#3396F1; width:200px; height:200px"&gt;&lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p><strong>CSS</strong></p>  <pre><code>.anchor1-animation.ng-enter, .anchor1-animation.ng-leave {   @include transition(all 50ms linear); }  .anchor1-animation.ng-anchor-out {   @include transition(all 0ms linear); }  .anchor1-animation.ng-anchor-in {   @include transition(all 800ms cubic-bezier(0.230, 1.000, 0.320, 1.000)); } </code></pre>  <p>This works on all browsers except on Safari, its driving me crazy!</p>  <p>It works on Chrome, Firefox, IE10+, Edge.</p>